1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:03,279
-Previously on The O. C. :
-You' re a tough kid from Chino...

2
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:06,830
...with an ex-girlfriend who's the
most beautiful girl ever in high school.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,788
-Yeah. But right now I'm here with you.
-He snuck out to see his girlfriend.

4
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:12,951
-What are we doing?
-I call it "prepping the oven. "

5
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:15,190
What are we doing
in the larger sense?

6
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:19,350
I'd like to place an order for delivery.

7
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:24,310
Can I get the crispy noodles
with shrimp and the calamari salad?

8
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:28,029
Get the Vietnamese rolls.
And the chicken with the spicy curry.

9
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:31,636
No, just one. And Vietnamese rolls
and chicken with spicy curry.

10
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:34,030
You guys want something
from Thaiphoon?

11
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,713
Yeah, some pad thai, please.

12
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:38,997
Y eah, Mom, will you order
a couple gallons of the tom yum soup?

13
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:42,152
And then the salmon with the
chili-lime sauce. And dumplings.

14
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:45,551
Okay, can we get some pad thai,
some tom yum soup...

15
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,029
-...salmon with the chili-lime sauce--
-Dumplings.

16
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,509
And the steamed dumplings.
Yeah. Great.

17
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,629
-We ordered enough for a small army.
-I got an idea.

18
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:55,791
Why don't you ask
your female cohorts over?

19
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:59,350
Lindsay's with her mom. Family therapy
and to a Truffaut retrospective.

20
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:03,149
That's a hell of a double-header.
What about Alex?

21
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,394
-Howdy.
-What are you doing here?

22
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:13,792
Okay, that's not the warmest greeting
I've ever received, but I will take it.

23
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:17,316
I didn't expect to see you here
right now. I'm kind of busy.

24
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:19,994
I wanted to invite you to have dinner
with the family.

25
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,718
I don't think it's a good idea.

26
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,997
My ex is in town.

27
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,350
Actually, in my office.

28
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,591
Waiting for me.

29
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,756
Your ex.

30
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:40,072
Well, part of the ABC's of the ex is
to step aside for the I and the U.

31
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:43,118
But the ex isn't technically an ex.

32
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:48,238
We never really broke up, officially.
It's part of what we need to figure out.

33
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,676
But I really do wanna come
have dinner with your family...

34
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:54,070
...so maybe we can do it
after the ex leaves.

35
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:57,118
Okay, so the ex is leaving.
When? Later tonight?

36
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,910
Staying the night. That's cool.
Staying the week?

37
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:03,470
I don't know. I didn't know
this was gonna happen, and now it has.

38
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:08,191
I have to deal with it. It would be great
if you could just let me figure it out.

39
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,999
Just, in other words, stay away
while the ex is in town.

40
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,714
Unless you're cool
with the three of us hanging out.

41
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:16,952
Okay, well, I'm gonna have
to get back to you on that.

42
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,431
I like the new club.

43
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,958
-You ready to get out of here?
-ln a minute.

44
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,835
-So what if Alex has an ex?
-Most people do.

45
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,639
That's right. He's probably just
some meathead thug...

46
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,872
...with her name tattooed
on his bicep.

47
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:31,031
Well, no threat to you.

48
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,519
Unless...

49
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,956
...he's a thug with a heart.

50
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:37,350
He's done his time,
1 8 months for robbery.

51
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,351
It was wrong. He understands that.

52
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,956
He's mature, he's sensitive, seasoned.

53
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:48,235
-So you're not okay.
-Not at all, Ryan. Not at all.

54
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,429
-He's spiraling, huh?
-Seth? He hasn't even begun.

55
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,113
-Hey.
-Hi, guys.

56
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:58,833
Marissa, that's an amazing skirt,
and I love your shoes.

57
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,310
Thanks. I really like your....

58
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,272
Your backpack.

59
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,238
Where's it from?

60
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,029
L.L. Bean.

61
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:16,190
Well, I'm late for class. But maybe
this weekend we can all hang.

62
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,238
-See a movie or go to Balboa lsland?
-Yeah, sounds great.

63
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,390
Every day, she looks like she could
be on the cover of a fashion magazine.

64
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,710
Yeah? I guess.

65
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:31,390
-Good thing I'm not competitive.
-What are you talking about?

66
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:34,632
Nothing. It's just, you know, you said it.
Everyone has an ex...

67
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:38,031
...and you seem to hang out
with yours a lot.

68
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,270
-We do?
-You do.

69
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:43,398
-Like, constantly.
-Maybe you two should become friends.

70
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:46,074
We can all hang out,
and it wouldn't be weird.

71
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:49,949
Yeah, me and the Cosmo Girl.
Yeah, that wouldn't be weird at all.

72
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,916
A massage.

73
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:03,952
-You must really need something.
-Favor. Tiny.

74
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:09,552
Ask me while you're giving me the
massage. I'm more inclined to say yes.

75
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,872
It's about work.

76
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:16,508
As you know, the Newport Group's
reputation is pretty much in the toilet.

77
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,399
-It's well-deserved.
-The board wants us to come up with...

78
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:23,394
...a plan to improve the company's
image. I figured who better to ask...

79
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:27,519
...than you, the man who practically
invented hating the Newport Group.

80
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,148
Well, I was doing it
long before it was trendy.

81
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,390
Yeah. So any ideas?

82
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:35,393
Yes. As a matter of fact, this is perfect.

83
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,676
-Perfect's good.
-I just got a call to work...

84
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:41,230
...with the Newport Housing lnitiative.
They want low-income housing.

85
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,995
-I was gonna petition the city council.
-The Newport Group can find the money.

86
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,355
Exactly. The housing board
gets a development.

87
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:51,195
And the company could do something
good for a change. Honey, that's perfect.

88
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,436
You've earned more than a massage.

89
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:57,230
Where I come from,
that only means one thing.

90
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:07,555
Hey. I have a surprise for you.

91
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:11,269
I love surprises. Especially when
they're named Jimmy Choo.

92
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,999
Am I about to get whacked?

93
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,031
Hey, a cupcake.

94
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,760
It doesn't have stiletto heels,
but I'll eat it anyway.

95
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,399
You know it's not my birthday.

96
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:25,711
Yes, and I also know
it's our six-month anniversary.

97
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:30,832
Oh, my God, it is.
God, it's been six months?

98
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,116
-Holy mack.
-I know, it's amazing.

99
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,635
I've never been in a relationship
this long.

100
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:39,270
-Neither have l.
-Well, I think we should celebrate.

101
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:43,513
I would like to take you to a romantic
anniversary dinner at The Arches.

102
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,159
What do you say?

103
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,395
So, what'd you say?

104
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,518
You know, that I'm fasting
for an upcoming colonoscopy.

105
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,875
I'm sure that was the answer
he was looking for.

106
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:57,316
Yes. Look, Zach is so unbelievably great.
But six months?

107
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,436
I did not even date Cohen that long.

108
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,512
When did we get so old?
When did life get so complicated?

109
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:06,036
I know. Remember when we were little,
and it was just you and me...

110
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,792
-...and the boys had cooties?
-Yeah.

111
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:10,793
And we had sleepovers and watched
Full House and Step by Step.

112
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,996
Oh, my God. I loved Full House.

113
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:16,232
But my favorite character was named
DJ, so I guess that's ruined.

114
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,436
No. Look, forget DJ.

115
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,716
Forget Cohen and Zach and Ryan.
You know what?

116
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:23,758
-We need a break from the boys.
-You mean a girls' night out?

117
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,753
I do. You telling me you couldn't use
a night without boys?

118
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,957
-Well, Full House is on Nick at Nite.
-Really?

119
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,439
Thanks.

120
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,558
So great news.

121
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:39,633
Sandy has an amazing idea to kick-start
an image makeover for the company.

122
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,872
-I have better news and a better idea.
-You haven't heard his yet.

123
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:46,316
It would be hard for Sandy's idea
to top the best idea ever.

124
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,119
-You ready?
-Probably not, no.

125
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:55,277
Oh, my--
There's so much you here.

126
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:59,633
A magazine, Kirsten, about Newport life,
restaurants, events, gossip.

127
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:03,077
Selling Newport Beach
as an aspirational brand.

128
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:06,357
Well, Sandy's idea,
which is in a different direction...

129
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:09,910
...involves funding
a low-income housing development.

130
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,674
That's kind of cute. I guess.

131
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:15,559
But, Kiki, we're trying to appeal
to the Newport elite.

132
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,756
We need to think about
who these people are:

133
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,036
Bored, rich gossipmongers
who like to shop.

134
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,792
They're me. And I don't care
about low-income housing.

135
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,512
You have a point.

136
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:30,880
-This is as far as I go.
-Thanks for walking me.

137
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,474
Have fun at your emergency
comic-book meeting.

138
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:36,438
Why do I get the feeling
Seth won't be talking about comics?

139
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,079
Yeah. You okay?

140
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,630
-Yeah, sure. I like eating alone.
-You know who you could sit with--

141
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,832
No. That's okay, really.

142
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,117
Get to know her, she'll stop being
my ex and become your friend.

143
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:50,238
Ryan, don't. Okay, please.
I'm sure they don't even eat.

144
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,435
-Hey.
-Hey.

145
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,638
You guys mind if Lindsay joins you?

146
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,598
-I gotta meet Seth.
-No. Emergency comic-book meeting?

147
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,352
-Zach was summoned too.
-You heard.

148
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:02,350
-Have a seat, Lindsay.
-Great. Thanks, you guys. See you.

149
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:08,715
This is so good. Great idea
hitting the drive-through for lunch.

150
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:12,316
It'll probably be hours on the elliptical
trainer working those off, huh?

151
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,676
Coop exercising? Now, that's funny.

152
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:20,318
So you guys can just eat cheeseburgers
and look like you?

153
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:23,199
No. Well, sometimes we get
chili fries too.

154
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,032
Why? What are you eating?

155
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,879
It's a Zone meal.
It's low-carb.

156
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,759
So we were planning our
girls' night out for this weekend.

157
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,792
Do you want to join us?

158
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,188
Me?

159
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,599
What do you say?

160
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,352
Okay. Sure.

161
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,717
So break it down for me, guys.
And don't afraid to be honest.

162
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:50,395
Well, what you should've done is
tell her, "Take all the space you need.

163
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,312
I know this must be hard. "

164
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:54,152
Boom! You're a hero.

165
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,436
You look confident,
but like you still care.

166
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,989
Yeah, that is so the way
I should've played it.

167
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,832
When do we discuss
The New Avengers?

168
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:04,552
Philip, your membership has been
revoked. You're not there for me.

169
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,234
-I'm not there for you. Beat it.
-He doesn't mean it.

170
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,994
-He's just upset.
-I don't care if you're in junior high.

171
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:13,391
I think you're onto something. I like it.
You know what? I'll call her.

172
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:16,279
-Tell her I'm giving her some space.
-Dude, don't do that.

173
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,111
-What's happening?
-He's calling her.

174
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,511
-Give me that.
-I'm leaving a message.

175
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,591
No, you are not.

176
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,799
Jeez, man. Fine. Whatever.

177
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:33,837
-Forget calling. I'll go down there.
-No.

178
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,434
If I'm losing her,
I wanna see who I'm losing her to.

179
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:39,831
-You are not going down there.
-I have to. My paycheck's down-- Yes.

180
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,436
Yes. That's perfect. She owes me $38.
I have to go down there.

181
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,511
Okay? How can I live
without that money?

182
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,432
-I gotta eat.
-What if I go down there?

183
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,670
-I come with you. Okay.
-I'll go down there.

184
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:53,150
I'll say I'm picking up your paycheck,
sniff around for the ex.

185
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:56,672
Okay. Check him out. Report back
to me. Maybe snap a few photos.

186
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,478
-Sure. What do you say?
-All right.

187
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,632
Listen. You gotta apologize to Philip.
He took that really hard.

188
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,314
Philip. He's always been the weak one.

189
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,995
Hey. Come on. I'm sorry what
happened back there. Heat of passion.

190
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,357
You know how it is? Sorry, sometimes
Bruce Banner turns into the Hulk.

191
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:18,639
Hey, I talked to the housing initiative.
They are on cloud nine over there.

192
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,789
Good.

193
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:23,748
They're gonna draw up a proposal
for you to bring to work. Okay, honey...

194
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:27,959
...I don't want to alarm you, but there is
a giant Julie Cooper on the table.

195
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:31,271
It's Julie's idea for an image makeover.
A magazine.

196
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,431
I'm assuming you nipped this one
in the bud.

197
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:37,036
Well, she did her homework.
Ran the numbers.

198
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:40,397
-The proposal wasn't bad.
-You're not considering this, are you?

199
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,353
Well, there's a lot of ideas
on the table, Sandy.

200
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:46,034
Well, when you shoot down hers,
be sure to toss this.

201
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,872
It's giving me the willies, okay?

202
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,431
Hi. Hi.

203
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,239
I'm here to pick up a paycheck.
Name's Cohen.

204
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:03,678
So you must be Alex's new guy.
The famous Seth Cohen.

205
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:08,039
No. I'm his friend, Ryan.
I'm just doing him a favor.

206
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,835
I really wanted to meet this Seth.

207
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,117
-Yeah?
-Yeah. I'm Jody.

208
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,875
You're the ex.

209
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:23,074
So you didn't see anything
at the club?

210
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:26,915
I mean, there were no shady guys
hanging around Alex's office?

211
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,071
Definitely didn't see any guys.

212
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,708
Are we meeting Zach here
or at the comic-book store?

213
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,916
Here. Now, you must have
seen someone.

214
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:37,311
Tell me this. Who gave you the check?
Tell me everything that happened.

215
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:41,234
In fact, better yet,
reenact it word for word. Go.

216
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,957
Zach. Hey.

217
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,917
How are you? So good to see you.

218
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,753
-How are you?
-Good. I'm good.

219
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:53,395
I'm terrible, actually.
I think I freaked Summer out.

220
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:55,596
I don't know. She bailed on our date.

221
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:58,433
Now she's doing a girls'-night-out thing
at the Bait Shop.

222
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,791
She's not returning
any of my phone calls.

223
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:03,235
I don't know. Maybe new comics
will ease the pain.

224
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:06,119
I feel that pain. Let's go down
to The Bait Shop tonight...

225
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:09,033
-...and talk to the girls.
-Or we could forget the girls.

226
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,156
Do our own thing.
Have a guys' night out.

227
