00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,794
Lindsay!

481
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:25,638
Lindsay!

482
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:27,793
Lindsay!

483
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,912
Lindsay!

484
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,352
Lindsay!

485
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:38,795
Lindsay!

486
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,878
Ryan! What are you doing?

487
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:51,436
Lindsay! She's out here somewhere!
Get help!

488
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:54,393
-Lindsay's fine!
-What?

489
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:55,754
I just saw her.

490
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:59,276
She's fine.
She's passed out in Alex's office.

491
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:06,596
She went looking for you, ran into
Marissa, who was doing the same thing.

492
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,432
Yeah? I can't wait to see her.

493
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,351
What happened to you?

494
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:18,117
-ls she okay?
-She'll be fine. She's just sleeping it off.

495
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:20,197
-I should get her home.
-I can do that.

496
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,152
-I think you've done enough.
-Okay.

497
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:24,276
This is the part
where you blame it on me?

498
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:27,392
You're right. It was Lindsay's idea
to pound vodka and pass out.

499
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:30,239
-Good to see someone else messed-up?
-lt was her idea.

500
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:34,109
-Okay, so it got a little out of control--
-lt always does with you.

501
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:37,392
You spent last year trying to
drag me down with you. And now her?

502
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,554
You want to make a mess
out of your own life? Fine!

503
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,631
Doing a good job of it, if you ask me.

504
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:49,796
-No one asked you.
-What did you say?

505
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,958
-Hey, Ryan, let's-- Let's go.
-I'm not leaving her here.

506
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:57,711
-I'll take care of her. You go.
-Yeah, come on. It'll be fine.

507
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:01,198
Ryan, let's go.

508
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:11,037
Just call and let us know she's okay.

509
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:21,157
Let's get her out of here.

510
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,115
Yeah.

511
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:36,079
Hey.
Black-and-white milk shake, please.

512
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,473
One.

513
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,638
Zach.

514
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:05,193
So...

515
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:08,319
...I'm sorry for being
Ultra Bitch 2000 tonight.

516
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:10,432
-Tonight?
-Fair enough.

517
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:14,429
It's just that
my whole dating experience...

518
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:18,718
...amounts to a six-month angst-fest
with Cuckoo for Cohen.

519
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:22,874
So when I'm with you,
someone who is sane and normal...

520
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:26,077
...it's like I was raised by wolves.

521
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,117
-Do you need the drama?
-Well, if by that you mean...

522
00:33:30,280 --> 00:33:33,352
...do I miss the wolves? No.

523
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:38,351
See, wolves, they pee all over the place
marking their territory. Gross.

524
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:43,994
But while I'm learning
how to not howl at the moon...

525
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:46,876
...I need to take baby steps.

526
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,878
-Like this anniversary thing--
-I got it.

527
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:52,393
And don't worry.

528
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:56,348
If we're still together when we hit
one year, I'm gonna totally blow it off.

529
00:33:56,680 --> 00:34:00,195
I think that is the sweetest thing
anyone has ever said to me.

530
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:18,077
Alex called. Lindsay's home.

531
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,519
Everything okay?

532
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:25,351
I assume so.
We didn't really have a long talk.

533
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:27,431
She hung up on me.

534
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:31,077
Which was maybe a hint
that I really screwed things up tonight.

535
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:34,750
I don't think me and Marissa
will be hanging out any time soon.

536
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:38,909
I was probably too hard on her, huh?

537
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:41,795
There were flashes
of the old Ryan Atwood.

538
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:45,310
It just brings back old issues,
you know. Marissa, my mom--

539
00:34:45,520 --> 00:34:47,670
You don't have to lump Lindsay
in that category.

540
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,871
She was probably just trying
to let loose.

541
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:51,792
Or Marissa pressured her into it.

542
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:57,319
I think if Lindsay was feeling pressure,
it was probably coming from you.

543
00:34:57,680 --> 00:35:00,513
I mean, you kind of shotgunned them
into that relationship.

544
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:03,195
But, I mean, the girlfriend
and the ex as friends?

545
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:05,591
I think that goes against nature.

546
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:09,676
-Someone could follow their own advice.
-Y eah.

547
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:13,312
Y eah, I should apologize.
It's just my pride.

548
00:35:14,640 --> 00:35:15,709
What pride?

549
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:18,678
-There's nothing standing in my way.
-You wanna drive or me?

550
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:19,989
-You.
-All right.

551
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:22,998
And now my wife has given us all
the opportunity to find out.

552
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:26,278
Ghosts, et cetera, being only
creations of hysteria....

553
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:28,192
-Hey.
-Hi.

554
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:33,355
I think everyone wonders
what they would do if they saw a ghost.

555
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:35,909
If you' re still angry,
you have every right to be.

556
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:39,710
No, well, that-- That's good to know.
But here's the thing.

557
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,279
I' m not angry at all.

558
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:45,991
Since I left the law firm, your father's
been grooming me to be his henchman...

559
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,197
...and I've been letting him.

560
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,873
I think, in some way...

561
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:53,869
-...I've been postponing the inevitable.
-And that is?

562
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:57,551
Figuring out what to do next.

563
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:01,313
Sandy, we can still
make your housing idea work.

564
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:04,074
I'm gonna go on record
recommending the project.

565
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:06,271
I appreciate that.

566
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,476
But I'd rather you didn't.

567
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:15,119
Julie's magazine will always
give me the heebie-jeebies.

568
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:18,073
And business-wise,
it's probably your best bet.

569
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:21,439
Besides, if I work with you...

570
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:24,876
...your father will ambush us
every time we try to have a date.

571
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:27,913
That was the worst date
we've ever had, wasn't it?

572
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:32,708
A double date with your father
and Julie Cooper.

573
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:35,713
Sounds like the plot of this movie.

574
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,393
Maybe we shouldn't both be here.

575
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:43,552
It's potentially too much apology
for one doorstep.

576
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:46,029
-We're not doing it at the same time.
-That's good.

577
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:48,998
I don't think the synchronized apology
would work.

578
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:57,353
It's like you're stalking me.

579
00:36:57,600 --> 00:37:00,512
Yeah. But I'm stalking
with good intentions.

580
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:03,872
-I came to apologize.
-So did l.

581
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:07,391
-Marissa's inside.
-Thanks.

582
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:11,716
And so is Jody. So you and me...

583
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,917
...are outside.

584
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:20,038
Hey.

585
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:30,472
Look, I don't know. I--

586
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:34,477
I was hoping this could be easy.
For you and me to stay friends...

587
00:37:34,640 --> 00:37:38,076
-...you and Lindsay to be friends--
-We all live happily ever after?

588
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:40,948
Yeah, something like that.

589
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:45,792
I know it seems like a million years ago
we dated. But it wasn't.

590
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:49,037
-I know that.
-And, okay, maybe you're over it.

591
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:52,038
Maybe it doesn't mean anything
to you anymore.

592
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,877
Maybe it never did.

593
00:37:58,880 --> 00:38:00,836
But it meant a lot to me.

594
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:04,431
You meant a lot to me.

595
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:06,591
You still do.

596
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,596
It's not like that. I....

597
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:16,150
I don't know what it's like. Thinking
you and Lindsay should be friends...

598
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:19,392
-...was a bad idea.
-Why? I like her.

599
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:23,714
And if you do the math,
she's my stepsister, so....

600
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,079
I guess.

601
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:36,919
Clearly, it's gonna be strange for us
for a while.

602
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:39,031
Yeah, I know. You're right.

603
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,830
I'm sorry.

604
00:38:50,240 --> 00:38:52,959
That's what I came here to say.

605
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,752
I'm sorry too.

606
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:07,790
So you and Jody?
You getting back together?

607
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:10,869
I doubt it.

608
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:13,960
She's kind of a pain in the ass.

609
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:16,993
-But maybe that's my type.
-Right.

610
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:21,274
So then, I mean, does that mean
we can go back to before? Because...

611
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:23,715
...I can forget this ever happened.

612
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,356
Okay. I'll wait.

613
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:32,240
Because that's what adults do.
They wait. So I'm waiting. Adult style.

614
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:34,873
Hey.

615
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:36,713
You ready?

616
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:41,153
Yeah.

617
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:43,117
I guess so.

618
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:49,709
Thanks for coming by.

619
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:53,357
And I'm sorry too.

620
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:09,596
At last, you've got it all.

621
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,756
Everything I have.

622
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:14,110
-Even my life.
-Hey.

623
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:16,709
-Jody went to sleep.
-Cool.

624
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:20,077
-I think we've seen the last of the guys.
-I wouldn't be so sure.

625
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:23,596
There's still, like, what,
four minutes of girls' night out left?

626
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:27,034
I've had enough of girls and guys.

627
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,550
There's an old horror movie on.

628
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:34,037
Works for me.

629
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:41,191
Are you cold?

